        <speech by="#50073f98-101e-4a05-aef5-b6739b325fb8">
          <from>HON. CHARLIE PARKER</from>
          <p>HON. CHARLIE PARKER : I want to thank all honourable members for their interventions, and I certainly also want to thank my colleague here beside me, the Minister of Communities, Culture and Heritage. You can certainly hear his passion, and he's worked long and hard on this to establish Sable Island as Canada's 43rd National Park. It will be Nova Scotia's third National Park, so it is important for our province.</p>
